General.Name: Diamyd Medical AB (publ)
General.Description: Diamyd Medical AB (publ) develops therapies for the treatment of autoimmune diabetes. The company develops Diamyd, an antigen-specific immunotherapy diabetes vaccine, which is in phase III clinical trial for the treatment of type 1 diabetes and latent autoimmune diabetes; and Remygen, an oral regenerative and immunomodulatory drug candidate, which is in phase I/II clinical trial for the treatment of autoimmune and type 2 diabetes. It has a research and development collaboration agreement with Juvenile Diabetes Research Foundation to develop DIAGNODE-3 Phase 3 trial in Type 1 diabetes. The company was formerly known as Diamyd Therapeutics AB and changed its name to Diamyd Medical AB (publ) in April 2013. Diamyd Medical AB (publ) was incorporated in 1984 and is based in Stockholm, Sweden.
